## Handoff Receiving Template

```
=== CURSOR HANDOFF PACKAGE ===
Project: [repo name]
Branch: [branch name]
Handed off from: [platform] ([phase completed])
Receiving: Cursor ([phase beginning])

--- .cursor/rules UPDATE ---
[Create or update .cursor/rules/current-task.md with:]

## Current Task
[What this Cursor session is for]

## Stack
[Language, framework, key dependencies]

## Conventions
[Naming, file structure, patterns to follow]

## Acceptance Criteria
[What "done" looks like — specific and verifiable]

## Do Not Modify
[Files, directories, patterns that must not change]

--- AGENT PROMPT ---
[Paste into Cursor Agent mode:]

You are continuing work on [project]. Here is the current state:

Completed:
- [What exists and works]

Your task:
1. [First action — reference file paths]
2. [Second action]
3. [Third action]

Constraints:
- [Hard constraint 1 — e.g., "Do not modify the database schema"]
- [Hard constraint 2]

Run tests after each significant change.

When complete, output:
- Files changed (list with one-line description of each change)
- Decisions made (and why)
- Blockers or unresolved questions
This will be used for: /handoff return from Cursor

=== END ===
```

## Configuration Checklist
- [ ] Update `.cursor/rules/current-task.md` before starting
- [ ] Confirm correct branch is checked out
- [ ] Select appropriate model for the task (Claude for quality, GPT for breadth, Gemini for large context)
- [ ] Use Agent mode (not Chat mode) for multi-file tasks
- [ ] Enable relevant MCP integrations if the task touches external tools (GitHub, Linear, Figma)
- [ ] For Background Agents: task must be well-defined with clear acceptance criteria before launching
